  "id": "guide/store-devtools",
  "title": "@ngrx/store-devtools",
  "contents": "\n\n\n  <div class=\"github-links\">\n    <a href=\"https://github.com/ngrx/platform/edit/main/projects/ngrx.io/content/guide/store-devtools/index.md?message=docs%3A%20describe%20your%20change...\" aria-label=\"Suggest Edits\" title=\"Suggest Edits\"><i class=\"material-icons\" aria-hidden=\"true\" role=\"img\">mode_edit</i></a>\n  </div>\n\n\n<div class=\"content\">\n<h1 id=\"ngrxstore-devtools\">@ngrx/store-devtools<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/store-devtools#ngrxstore-devtools\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h1>\n<p>Store Devtools provides developer tools and instrumentation for <a href=\"guide/store\">Store</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"installation\">Installation<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/store-devtools#installation\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<p>Detailed installation instructions can be found on the <a href=\"guide/store-devtools/install\">Installation</a> page.</p>\n<h2 id=\"setup\">Setup<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/store-devtools#setup\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<p>Instrumentation with the Chrome / Firefox Extension</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Download the <a href=\"https://github.com/reduxjs/redux-devtools/\">Redux Devtools Extension</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Provide the <code><a href=\"api/store-devtools/provideStoreDevtools\" class=\"code-anchor\">provideStoreDevtools</a></code> to the application config:</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<code-example header=\"main.ts\">\n<a href=\"api/store-devtools/DevToolsFeatureOptions#import\" class=\"code-anchor\">import</a> { isDevMode } from '@angular/core';\n<a href=\"api/store-devtools/DevToolsFeatureOptions#import\" class=\"code-anchor\">import</a> { bootstrapApplication } from '@angular/platform-browser';\n<a href=\"api/store-devtools/DevToolsFeatureOptions#import\" class=\"code-anchor\">import</a> { <a href=\"api/store/provideStore\" class=\"code-anchor\">provideStore</a> } from '@ngrx/store';\n<a href=\"api/store-devtools/DevToolsFeatureOptions#import\" class=\"code-anchor\">import</a> { <a href=\"api/store-devtools/provideStoreDevtools\" class=\"code-anchor\">provideStoreDevtools</a> } from '@ngrx/store-devtools';\n\n<a href=\"api/store-devtools/DevToolsFeatureOptions#import\" class=\"code-anchor\">import</a> { AppComponent } from './app.component';\n\nbootstrapApplication(AppComponent, {\n  providers: [\n    <a href=\"api/store/provideStore\" class=\"code-anchor\">provideStore</a>(),\n    <a href=\"api/store-devtools/provideStoreDevtools\" class=\"code-anchor\">provideStoreDevtools</a>({\n      <a href=\"api/store-devtools/StoreDevtoolsConfig#maxAge\" class=\"code-anchor\">maxAge</a>: 25, // Retains last 25 states\n      <a href=\"api/store-devtools/StoreDevtoolsConfig#logOnly\" class=\"code-anchor\">logOnly</a>: !isDevMode(), // Restrict extension to log-only mode\n      <a href=\"api/store-devtools/StoreDevtoolsConfig#autoPause\" class=\"code-anchor\">autoPause</a>: true, // Pauses recording actions and state changes when the extension window is not open\n      <a href=\"api/store-devtools/StoreDevtoolsConfig#trace\" class=\"code-anchor\">trace</a>: false, //  If set to true, will include stack <a href=\"api/store-devtools/StoreDevtoolsConfig#trace\" class=\"code-anchor\">trace</a> for every dispatched action, so you can see it in <a href=\"api/store-devtools/StoreDevtoolsConfig#trace\" class=\"code-anchor\">trace</a> tab jumping directly to that part of code\n      <a href=\"api/store-devtools/StoreDevtoolsConfig#traceLimit\" class=\"code-anchor\">traceLimit</a>: 75, // maximum stack <a href=\"api/store-devtools/StoreDevtoolsConfig#trace\" class=\"code-anchor\">trace</a> frames to be stored (in case <a href=\"api/store-devtools/StoreDevtoolsConfig#trace\" class=\"code-anchor\">trace</a> option was provided as true)\n      <a href=\"api/store-devtools/StoreDevtoolsConfig#connectInZone\" class=\"code-anchor\">connectInZone</a>: true // If set to true, the connection is established within the Angular zone\n    })\n  ],\n});\n</code-example>\n<blockquote>\n<p>More extension options and explanation, refer to <a href=\"https://github.com/reduxjs/redux-devtools#documentation\">Redux Devtools Documentation</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n\n</div>\n\n<!-- links to this doc:\n - docs\n - guide/data/entity-actions\n - guide/store/why\n-->\n<!-- links from this doc:\n - api/store-devtools/DevToolsFeatureOptions#import\n - api/store-devtools/StoreDevtoolsConfig#autoPause\n - api/store-devtools/StoreDevtoolsConfig#connectInZone\n - api/store-devtools/StoreDevtoolsConfig#logOnly\n - api/store-devtools/StoreDevtoolsConfig#maxAge\n - api/store-devtools/StoreDevtoolsConfig#trace\n - api/store-devtools/StoreDevtoolsConfig#traceLimit\n - api/store-devtools/provideStoreDevtools\n - api/store/provideStore\n - guide/store\n - guide/store-devtools#installation\n - guide/store-devtools#ngrxstore-devtools\n - guide/store-devtools#setup\n - guide/store-devtools/install\n - https://github.com/ngrx/platform/edit/main/projects/ngrx.io/content/guide/store-devtools/index.md?message=docs%3A%20describe%20your%20change...\n - https://github.com/reduxjs/redux-devtools#documentation\n - https://github.com/reduxjs/redux-devtools/\n-->"
